article_title: Campaigning Democrats Oppose Fast-Track for Obama
article_text:
WASHINGTON—All six House Democrats who have announced runs for the Senate next year oppose a bill granting President Barack Obama fast-track trade negotiating authority, an indication of the issue’s political potency as the trade debate intensifies in the House.

The measure, which the president could use to expedite a trade deal with Japan and 10 other Pacific Rim nations through Congress, isn’t popular with some of the more liberal...
